ai-patthana23.19:0.2_0: under the investigation of principles means to the extent of the Dhamma.
ai-patthana23.19:0.3_0: Seeing their vows, doing good deeds,
ai-patthana23.19:1.1_0: Not skilled in loss of focuses, or practices,
ai-patthana23.19:2.1_0: Not for the sake of unprofitableness, or for extra effort.
ai-patthana23.19:3.1_0: One has not declared untroubled only Dhamma. It has no cause or condition.
ai-patthana23.19:4.1_0: One is not skilled in being unskilled in learning, nor doing what is unskillful, nor what is not indeterminate, nor what is beneficial, nor what is not specific.
ai-patthana23.19:5.1_0: One is not skilled in loss of focus, and has not got rid of repulsion.
ai-patthana23.19:6.1_0: One is not skilled in loss of focus, or of not he has nothing to do with the flood.
ai-patthana23.19:6.1_1: This is the section in brief.
ai-patthana23.19:8.1_0: One is not skilled in loss of focus, and has no cause or condition.
ai-patthana23.19:9.1_0: Not for the skilled in loss of focus, or for the impingement, and for the sake of non-arising of repulsion.
ai-patthana23.19:9.1_1: ‘... for the sake of conditioned things.’ ...
ai-patthana23.19:9.1_2: There are three more mendicants who have no regrets.
